This paper proposes a new model for knowledge graph embedding (KGE) that addresses a specific problem with symmetric relations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which includes topics related to machine learning and reasoning. The paper also involves experiments and evaluations, which suggest that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. Additionally, the paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and semantic information, which could place it under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of datasets and benchmarks also suggests a possible categorization under cs.DB (Databases) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
